      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Tricky. KHALEESI'S DREAM (8) ran on well to place on debut over 1200m at this track. She'd been well educated and Byrne Burke stays aboard. Sure to improve and can get off the mark. DENNYSON (1) finished just behind the above in that contest racing forward. Fitter again and keeps the handy 3kg claim. He should be right in it. WALKING STREET (4) was on debut and had no luck at the start in the same race as a $3.5 favourite. Had come off a big Hobart trial win and, notwithstanding the awkward gate, deserves another chance. LUCKY COUNTRY (2) resumes and two back just missed this track/trip on debut when heavily backed. Won her latest trial and keep very safe.",
